<title>CHINA: HK May retail sales up 10 pct in value on yr.</title>
<headline>HK May retail sales up 10 pct in value on yr.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1997-07-25</dateline>
<text>
<p>Hong Kong's May retail sales totalled a provisional HK$19.7 billion, up 10 percent in value on the year and up six percent on the month, Census and Statistics Department figures showed.</p>
<p>The following are provisional percentage changes in the value and volume of all retail outlets:</p>
<p>						     May	April</p>
<p> Total retail sales (on-year)  - value   +10	 +9</p>
<p>					 - volume  +6	  +5</p>
<p>			  (on-month) - value   +6	  -2</p>
<p>					 - volume  +5	  -3</p>
<p>Breakdown by category (on-year)</p>
<p> Clothing and footwear	   - value   +5	  +4</p>
<p>					 - volume  -4	  -6</p>
<p>Jewellery, watches</p>
<p> clocks, valuable gifts	  - value   +17	 +15</p>
<p>					 - volume  +18	 +26</p>
<p>Consumer durables,</p>
<p> excluding cars		    - value   +11	 +7</p>
<p>					 - volume  +9	  +5</p>
<p> Department stores		 - value   +10	 +5</p>
<p>					 - volume  +2	  -4</p>
<p> Supermarkets			- value   +12	 +10</p>
<p>					 - volume  +3	  +2</p>
<p> Fuels				 - value   +9	  +6</p>
<p>					 - volume  +3	  -1</p>
<p> Motor vehicles		    - value   +21	+46</p>
<p>					 - volume  +20	+46</p>
<p>Food, alcoholic drinks and</p>
<p> tobacco			     - value   +4	  -2</p>
<p>					 - volume  +4	  +2</p>
<p>** = virtually unchanged</p>
<p>-- Hong Kong Newsroom (852) 2843 6441</p>
